caption: The food is so good and the employees are so sweet.
Awesome staff, only topped by the food which is so well made. The pickling work done on the veggies included are alone enough a reason to visit this place.
The service and the food is always excellent every time. The staff is very friendly and the food taste amazing!!
Excellent customer service. High-quality flavors and ingredients. They also have awesome sauces.
Epic. Amazing flavors and textures and I walked away satiated.
Great food amazing service! Highly recommend.
They have the very best burgers and egg rolls.
Had the beyond meat tacos and it was amazing. That's coming from someone who's been eating and making tacos for as long as I can remember.
Had the impossible burger with fried pickles.  It's legit.
The appetizers are sooo good! I recommend the tater tots and fried pickles.
Love the burger and the 🍉 punch. Not to crazy about the 🍟..

I opened the box and saw how packed the box was. I took some photos of the fries to send to my sister since she had them before and recommended the roasted onion aioli sauce. I took a fry out and ate it. It was different. I took another to eat to figure out the taste. My brother in law said it was brine in pickle juice. Very interesting. I also tried the sauce and it was good. Also tried the comeback sauce. I was eating them and then my sister comes home and clearly I forgot to send her the photos. If you're looking for crunchy fries, these aren't but they weren't exactly soggy. It's a bit addictive. Fries tasted good with and without the sauce. I also got their watermelon lemonade. It came in a cool plastic bag that stands up. You can zip it up when you're not drinking it. You tasted both the watermelon and lemonade. I forgot to shake it so it was sour from the lemonade haha
Honestly ordered this beyond meatless vegetarian burger by mistake and was pleasantly surprised how good it tasted. Definitely check out all their sweet and sour pickle options!

Nice fast-food representation of what the Pickle Guys next door has to offer! awesome flare of pickled flavors, and with the dishes being meat-free you never feel too heavy afterwards. The Loaded Tots are truly loaded with flavor... and if you order nothing else, the Brined Fries are a MUST.
Loved it
Staff is friendly food is straight up delicious definitely one of if nothing my favorite  kosher/vegetarian place in the city

Absolutely love this place! Staff is always friendly and food comes out quickly! Fried pickles here are the best and unlike other places, they keep overnight. Don't sleep on the sauces either. It's worth paying a few bucks extra to get more. Pro-tip: Make sure you get an mask!
Love it!
Best. Service. Food. Ever!!

I found my people! Ferments, veg menu, and fabulous guys in the kitchen and next door packing pickles. My sister and I split the beyond burger combo, fried pickles, and both the watermelon and pineapple lemonades. We also had a generous helping of sauces that were all delicious (thanks Mike for making a fresh batch of aioli for us!). Be sure to drop next door to take home a few pints - the onions, mango, and hot sours are all out of this world! Way to make it kosher! Definitely will be back.
Great food and spot!
Best pickles ever,  they think of everything!
All the food is vegetarian and fantastic! Favorites are the deep fried pickles, because of course, and the pickled pineapple lemonade, one of the most unique drinks I’ve ever had.
Their Tacos put the "ill" in "Diller." ill = Sick = awesome
Stumbled across this amazing completely by accident and could not be happier. The owner was delightful and the food was incredible (as was the Pickle Monster drink). Can’t wait to come back!

The absolute best fried pickles in the city! And don’t even get me started on the egg roll and Pickle Monster. The owner was so nice and cracked us up. He was multitasking between phone orders and customers seated at tables, and still attended to us very quickly, and checked back to see how everything was. That’s not service you get at a little to go place! Dillers is my new favorite stop!!!

Really wonder spot. The food is so delicious and the service was exceptional. I wanted a pickle and the manager went next door to get me one from the pickle guys. So sweet and hospitable. loved the loaded tater tots so addictive
The brine fries are my weakness. They are delicious. I love to get the comeback sauce to dip.
Delish! Original food made to order ... quick and friendly service. What more can you ask for? Can’t wait to come back.
I loved this place so much. Great food and great service definitely recommend.
10/10 would recommend! Good fresh hot fried pickles are hard to find and these guys are on point! The Sriracha Aioli sauce with it was great👌🏾
Loved this place

This place had been on my radar for some time. While I didn't have a lot of time, and no where near enough room in my stomach, I was overwhelmed with the description and pictures of the Okra Rice balls and Rueben Egg Roll.  They were everything I had imagined and more. The pairing of sauces is impeccable. The Sriracha Aioli and Onion Aioli were perfect with each.  I'm planning my next pre-flight excursion to include a Beyond Burger and the signature Fried Pickles.  This is NOT a snack bar as listed with Google. While you can grab a snack they have a full meal menu with spectacular flavor combinations.  They are also very dietary conscious.  They offer vegan, gluten free, and Kosher options.  Well worth the time if you have it.
Amzing food crazy good people there and just tastes fresh and wholesome
I got the fried pickle chips and another customer bought me one of the burgers! Both were utterly delicious. Amazing customer service and a lot of fun for a little shop!
ALWAYS AWESOME!!!

Well let's see the fried pickles could be better and I have taste better so I am a little disappointed. My wife had the Orka rice balls she didn't like it I thought it was okay. The egg roll for me had a bad taste but my wife liked it. So the verdict is basically two star's.
Ultimately a pallet party for your taste buds.  Go fried pickles!!!
Great hidden gem that is for vegetarian.  Great concept and drinks.  I love pickles and they use fresh ingredients right next door.  Big support and love to the owner.  Must try.
Just had the best vegetarian tacos in the city here!
Best fried pickles I've ever had and excellent service! Can easily say I'll be coming here more often.  p.s. chips > spears
Need more star's this place is so good
Great service and great food! Everything was so flavorful and fresh.  The portions are perfect and the tacos are an absolute must.. will definitely be back! :))))
Great burgers and foods recommend their beyond burger combo fries and with watermelon Lemonade so delicious.

Finally got a chance to go here after what seems like years since I saw they were planning on opening. Their beyond burger was amazing as well their fried pickles. I was planning on sharing their watermelon lemonade drink but after 2 sips, I had to get one for myself. We didn't like their fries much but it wasn't bad either. Overall , we def plan to come back many more times
Great place with unique flavors. Amazing customer service. You have to try the pickled French fries.
Unusual fast foods you won't find anywhere else.  Worth a visit.
Yummo vegetarian place...
There food is so amazing
Interesting, eclectic fried noshes.
Great fried potatoe pickled. Unique taste.

They went above and beyond with my pregnancy cravings! I’ve been a vegetarian for 5 years and been craving a cheese burger but because of Diller? I will not reconsider eating a cheese burger again! So kind and welcoming! Thank you Diller!
Great food
You have to try their fried pickles.
Do yourself a favor and try the pickled pineapple lemonade!
OMG!! Sooo good! Delicious and fresh and oh so tasty.
Lovely staff, amazing food and drinks. Every time.
Great food. Might clog your arteries.
Great vegetarian place with awesome items...Try the Reuben Egg Rolls!
Best fried pickles ever and I love fried pickles. Great vegan options. Delish lemonade . Funny people.
Fried pickle fries, a must try

Really enjoyed the excellent fried pickles and rice balls at this small counter service restaurant.  The staff was engaging and did a good job describing the sauces available.  It's kosher certified and there's a sink for hand washing if you get something with bread.
Best fried pickles I've ever had. Quality ingredients, very friendly staff. Try the okra balls too!
Do you like fried pickles? This is the spot!! Also their lemonades with pickle juice are surprisingly delightful!

Easily the best pickle chips I have ever had! I suggest trying the chipotle sauce with them for a little sweetness and a little kick. Friendly staff and quick service, this place is definitely worth checking out.
The BEST fried pickles I’ve ever had. Breading and seasoning are perfect! Pair with the chipotle sauce, it’s so good. The guy working there was so great! Great atmosphere.
The food is delicious and looks even better than it does on Instagram definitely will be back.
Great nachos and fried pickles. Everything is vegetarian and kosher
Amazing place! Great late night spot! Staff is really nice and food is very unique :)

I had the most delicious meal at Diller in LES, and the best part is it was all vegetarian and kosher, just like their entire menu! There are also vegan options included if that's your preference. The beyond burger was juicy and flavorful and is made from scratch (except the bun and patty). The fried pickles are made fresh using pickles from The Pickle Guys right next door. Also, they serve 2 types of lemonade which are made with their homemade pickled fruits. I highly recommend trying the watermelon lemonade! They are currently running a promotion on Sundays in which you can get a free lemonade when placing an order, if you follow their IG account.

I always look forward to working on my Thursdays because I know it means I get to eat here.  Not only is the food phenomenal (seriously I will never buy a regular burger again after you guys) but the staff are incredible. There are not a lot of places that can provide both quality food and service, but I'm sure glad this one does. See y'all next week!
Great food and great service - Armando is a legend!
These guys are killing it. Literally the entire menu is killer
Dope kosher pickle spot!
Food is fried but very good and generous portion on their fries

The popular fried pickles chips are gluten free and vegan y'all and they are worth every last delicious bite. Seasoned to perfection and paired with ketchup, it is the perfect afternoon snack! Love love loved it. Also the owner is the nicest guy I've ever ran into on NYC - bless that man and all his hard pickle work.
Absolutely phenomenal!!!
Can’t go wrong with Diller. Awesome food and great vegetarian options. The fellas behind the counter were excellent. Friendly and fun and great all around
Great food, even better service. Food is affordable and unique.

Pickled theme fast food joint serving up a small yet delicious selection of burgers and fries. All of the food is prepared on order, so it's guaranteed fresh and hot. First time having a "beyond meat" type burger, and I have to say, the texture and flavor and very comparable to animal-based protein. The space itself is small with limited indoor and outdoor seating.
WOW, what a hidden little gem attached to a pickle joint.  Had the rice balls, just burting with flavor, and gooey cheese.  The burger was good as well.
Delicious- short menu, perfectly executed.
Everything was great. I live in Memphis, and those were the best fried pickles I've had.

My favorite eatery in the neighborhood. Best fried pickles. My favorite is the combo, worthy every penny and is delicious. I was lucky enough to tried their secret menu and everything was awesome. Will be a forever fan of Diller!

A truly fantastic addition by the Pickle Guys. The lemonade is delicious and tart, the burger is ok/pretty good but the fries...my God the fries are exceptional. All their sauces are made in house too.
Great
Amazing food. Great service!
Great food! Sauces were awesome. Highly recommend the burger, egg roll, and of course - the fried pickles!
What an amazing and friends staff! As a pickle lover, this is the place to be!!
Yummy in the tummy burger and fried pickles
Got the fried pickles. I liked that they were different. They are slices and not spears. With their own spice mix sprinkled on top. Came out piping hot from the fryer.

Hungry after visiting Sargent’s Daughters on a September Wednesday night, we came across Dillers!  No meat establishment that is all about brine and pickle-ish food.  Mike and Armando were gracious and friendly - smiles and good cheer.  The pickle juice/cucumber juice/sake “monster” drink was EPIC!  Brined fries were so good (with the caraway dip especially).  Also devoured the brined rice balls and meatless pastrami egg roll. You might walk past and think “too small”.... but don’t!   Nice seating outside.  They are closed on all Jewish holidays and always on Saturdays, so plan your visit right.

What a refreshing new place to eat Diller is and right next to my favorite pickle spot. I'm happy The Pickle Guys decided to make an extension on something they've been cornering the market on! It's great for a quick bite or with a group of friends. Although space is limited, the park is just a block away and you're able to enjoy their delicious food on the benches. Amazing to see them develop something you just don't get around the Lower East Side.  My favorite is (of course) their signature fried pickles as well as the rice balls. Brine fries is a close 3rd to my list. Beyond Burger is a nice touch with its popularity. I've been trying to cut down on meat and it's a nice substitute. All in all, I'm grateful for their hard work and will happily recommend to anyone. Great food and staff! Keep up the good work fellas!

Diller’s fried and pickled dishes are delicious and incredibly filling. Even the brined French fries have just the right tang to be not only different, but really tasty. They have an excellent choice of sauces to keep things interesting and the portion sizes are generous, especially considering the reasonable prices (I believe almost everything on the menu is under $10). The folks who work here are also super friendly and personable which I always find to be a big positive. I highly recommend Diller if you have a large appetite. This place is not for those seeking a light snack because you won’t find it here.

Diller has set the bar so high for fried pickles that I'm afraid I won't want them from anywhere but here! I also tried their Rice Balls and Reuben Egg Roll and both were soooo delicious. It's as if they knew exactly what people would like and presented us with exactly that. This place and all of their menu items are a must try in LES!
They were so nice and helpful, told us some history of pickles in LES. The food was fantastic, couldn't even finish it. Those fried jalapenos were great!

Gluten free & dairy free options! Best gluten free pickles I've ever had. Friendly staff and some outdoor seating. Walk up counter to order / carry out.  Restaurant is new so not crazy busy yet but it will be! Egg roll & sauerkraut balls were delicious.

Such a great place, even ketchup was tasteful! Pickled Pineapple Lemonade is absolutely amazing, meatless Beyond Burger rocks and highly recommended, also it were one of the best brined fries I’ve ever tried. Staff is helpful and quick.
Food was delicious and very unique tastes
Excellent food

LOVE the food and energy in this terrific Lower East Side kosher restaurant! Brined fries are a revelation - crispy outside, soft inside, incredibly flavorful. Picked pineapple lemonade is so good they should bottle it.

Their fried pickles were amazing! Was nice and fast, and the cashier was warm and welcoming. My only complaint was about their website. Having seen the cashier and chefs’ merch, I went to their website to see if I could purchase some. Little did I know their website was incomplete. However, I will definitely recommend this restaurant and come back again.
The food itself 5 star I deftly would eat there again. The drinks well  I'd say there an acquired taste if you like pickle back shots then you'll love them...

Small menus generally mean higher quality and Diller is no exception. The fried pickles were perfect, the fries were some of the best I've had, and the the pickled pineapple lemonade was just incredible. We tried 5 or 6 of the sauces and they were all amazing, I'd recommend the honey mustard or the xxx death sauce. Also, the atmosphere is really nice and the guys working there were very friendly. We had such a great time and can't wait to go back!
Reccomend visiting that place, staff is really cool, the food is perfect, you will fall in love with pickels after your visit.
Pickles are breaded like frozen chicken nuggets Thick slices Lots of sauces Eggroll is dope af Also they got a pickled drink for $8
Weak service
Friendly staff and delicious dillers! Pickle Monster drink was also fire 🔥

The fried pickles are crispy and DELICIOUS! Most fried pickles around the neighborhood are soggy and gross. All the sauces are great too! If you like pickles and fried pickles come here!  Really interested in the beyond burger. It looks really good.  And the people who work here are really great and nice!
Just awesome food
Amazing food and service.

Delicious vegetarian kosher place. Good staff. Highly recommend the rice balls. The burger has a nice kick to it, and if you want real spice, go with the death sauce. Divine!!!  OH and their drinks are crazy. The pickled lemonade has a nice kick to it too, and the watermelon lemonade is also great. A little less tangy so it's more palatable for the general public.  Get everything and then go down the block to Doughnut Plant for an amazing selection of desserts!
Showed that fried pickles can actually be good
Best burger ever and it’s meatless which is unbelievable. The fries were also out of this world. My son loved the watermelon drink too.
Vegetarian Fried Pickles!

In a city that has every food imaginable, fried pickles are surprisgly lacking. Or... fried pickles were lacking, but now there's Diller.  Great staff, nice open-front location, and tasty food. Fried pickles were excellent -- the batter didn't drop off, which is always the test for fried pickles. Lots of dipping sauce options.  I look forward to going back and trying the rest of the menu.
This stuff is good!!!    Full of taste, nothing bland here... Even the fries are so tasty that they can be enjoyed plain..  Do not miss the watermelon lemonade!   Super friendly staff as well..
Delicious fried pickles and the rice balls are sooo yummy! Gotta go!👍🏼😉
Great customer service very friendly and kind the food is amazing. You have to try this place out😀
Great customer service! Food is different, in a good way!
Food was great. Beyond burger was incredible. Loved every bite. Staff was really cool. Will definitely come back!
Great!

Went there on opening night. Tried the beyond burger, fries pickles, rice balls, and the pickled pineapple lemonade. The burger was BEYOND amazing. Fried pickles were perfectly crunchy and the lemonade was super refreshing. Staff was super friendly. Can’t wait to go back and try the items they ran out of!
Absolutely delicious. Great, friendly service too!

Yum! Food was delicious. Beyond Burger is an absolute Must! The fried pickles were scrumptious and the sauces were on point. The store has a very cozy lower east side type of feel to it with outdoor space available. Two thumbs up.
